# Memory Tools

## When .venom/ Is Missing

If `.venom/` or `.venom/CONTEXT.md` is missing: do not read or write memory paths. Offer: "No workspace yet. Run `/venom init` to scaffold `.venom/`." Then run `/venom init` if owner confirms.

## Load

- `.venom/CONTEXT.md` — project brain: who, stack, focus, navigation
- `.venom/memory/MEMORY.md` — persistent context: decisions, patterns, corrections
- `.venom/learnings/preferences.yaml` — how owner likes to work
- `.venom/learnings/project.yaml` — project conventions
- `.venom/learnings/corrections.yaml` — hard corrections: never do X
- `.venom/work/ACTIVE.md` — what's in flight right now

Load when: onboarding (`/venom?`), vague request, repeated topic, referencing past work.

## Recall

When request references past work or decisions: read `.venom/memory/MEMORY.md` and `.venom/learnings/corrections.yaml` before answering. Don't answer from scratch if memory holds it.

## Save

- Corrections → `.venom/learnings/corrections.yaml`
- New conventions → `.venom/learnings/project.yaml` (with user confirmation)
- Decisions / patterns / preferences → `.venom/memory/MEMORY.md` (via `/venom remember`)

Never auto-save without user signal or explicit request.

## Work Lifecycle

Temp files created during a session → put in `.venom/work/[feature]/`.
When done: offer "Ship to docs? Or delete?" Never leave temp files floating.
